post_text: COVID-19 recovery cannot happen without a strong fiscal commitment to our schools. That’s why I’m calling for Mayor Bowser to stand by her commitment to support DC schools in fiscal year 2021. This must be paired with increased funding for the most vulnerable students and expanded access to behavioral health supports, mental health professionals, and trauma-informed instructional practices. Our students need more support when our school doors reopen, and the budget must help meet these needs. #DCSchoolsRecovery

post_text:
A number of families have reached out inquiring how they can help other members of the DCI community who may be struggling during this trying time. In response, we've created the DCI Community Fund to support our families.

If you are interested in making a donation toward the needs of DCI families severely impacted by COVID-19 closures, please make your donation here: dcinternationalschool.square.site

Thank you to those who have already donated. It is truly amazing to be a part of a community that bands together through hardships and uncertainty. We thank you for exhibiting the kindness and compassion that we strive to impart in our students. We are here for each other.
